value.title: 'Shoot your shot': Obama nails three-pointer while campaigning with Biden in Michigan
value.excerpt: Barack Obama called game.

value.title: Trump announces day of remembrance for Americans killed by illegal immigrants
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday declared Nov. 1 a day of remembrance for Americans killed by illegal immigrants -- seeking to highlight his policies curbing illegal immigration in the last days of his reelection campaign.

value.title: California pastor explains Trump vote with 'clear conscience'
value.excerpt: California pastor Bill Johnson of Bethel Church explains why he is voting for President Trump with 'confidence' after comparing his record to Joe Biden's.

value.title: Trump tells supporters in Pennsylvania they can 'save the American Dream' from 'corrupt forces'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Saturday told supporters in Pennsylvania that they have the chance to “save the American dream” by reelecting him to office on Tuesday -- while warning of “corrupt forces” who are seeking to replace him with Democratic nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Kayleigh McEnany says SEALs' rescue of American hostage is 'story of' Trump presidency: 'We don't stop'
value.excerpt: The American hostage rescued in West Africa by SEAL Team 6 in a daring raid is part of President Trump's exceptional accomplishments, Kayleigh McEnany said Saturday.

value.title: VP Mike Pence, Stacey Abrams, Jill Biden campaign in NC
value.excerpt: Three political figures will be stopping in North Carolina on Saturday to campaign for the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Ivanka Trump says she is 'unapologetically' pro-life
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump this week said that she is “unapologetically” pro-life, adding that motherhood changed how she thinks about the abortion issue.

value.title: In Miami, coalition of Latino evangelical leaders endorses Biden
value.excerpt: One pastor said that although the coalition is a nonprofit and nonpartisan, “in moments of crisis, the church has to unite the people.”

value.title: Top two pro-Trump super PACs make final $20 million ad push
value.excerpt: The two leading super PACs that are supporting President Trump's re-election bid are teaming up to shell out $20 million to run ads on TV and digital in seven crucial general election battleground in the closing stretch leading up to Election Day on Tuesday.

value.title: Facebook manually limited New York Post Hunter Biden story: Report
value.excerpt: Facebook fact-checkers manually flagged and restricted distribution of the New York Post's Hunter Biden story, documents obtained by The Guardian show.

value.title: Scott Walker claims Trump has 'fighting chance' in Wisconsin, touts Favre endorsement of president
value.excerpt: President Trump has a "fighting chance" to pull off a surprise victory in Wisconsin, repeating his feat of four years ago, former Republican Gov. Scott Walker told "Your World" Friday.

value.title: Pence returns to Arizona for final push to flip liberal-leaning cities
value.excerpt: In an effort to pick up voters from more progressive counties that voted against the president in 2016, Vice President Mike Pence is returning to the key battleground state of Arizona on Friday.

value.title: NFL legend Brett Favre endorses Trump for president
value.excerpt: NFL great Brett Favre has endorsed President Donald Trump for reelection. He's one of the most prominent figures in sports to publicly pledge support for the President.

value.title: Pence To Hold Rallies In Flagstaff, Tucson On Friday: Livestreams
value.excerpt: With four days to go until Election Day, Vice President Mike Pence returns to Arizona to rally support from voters.

value.title: Criscrossing Texas: In U.S. Senate race, Hegar joins Kamala Harris, Cornyn rolls with Ted Cruz
value.excerpt: U.S. Sen. John Cornyn and his challenger, former Air Force pilot MJ Hegar, are getting some big-name boosts in the final stretch of their Senate race

value.title: John James slams Michigan Senate opponent, says Dems 'freaking out' as Biden, Obama storm state
value.excerpt: Michigan Senate candidate John James reacts on 'Fox & Friends' to Joe Biden and former President Barack Obama campaigning in his state.

value.title: With time short, Vice President Mike Pence returns in effort to keep Arizona red
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will campaign in Flagstaff and Tucson as the presidential race in battleground Arizona goes down to the wire.

value.title: Candace Owens on Lil Wayne's Trump support: Liberals laughed at idea of 'Black Exit' by Dems
value.excerpt: Black Americans leaving the Democratic Party shows they have done nothing for the Black community, according to author Candace Owens on Friday.

value.title: Column: White House of Horrors: A Halloween-themed poem about Donald Trump
value.excerpt: The latest TrumPoem, a rhyming account of the presidency of Donald J. Trump, loosely based on his words and acts.

value.title: Pence highlights economic recovery report at Nevada rally
value.excerpt: RENO, Nev. (AP) — Vice President Mike Pence urged early in-person voting and highlighted reports of a partial economic recovery during a rally Thursday in Reno, hoping to drum up enthusiasm in Nevada in the final days before the election.

value.title: Facebook admits it 'improperly' blocked some political ads due to 'technical issues' as Joe Biden's campaign slams it for being 'wholly unprepared'
value.excerpt: Facebook said no ads were blocked "because of any partisan consideration," as Biden's camp accused the company of offering "no clarity" on the issue.

value.title: ‘People Are Going To Be Shocked’: Return of the ‘Shy’ Trump Voter?
value.excerpt: In 2016, pollsters Arie Kapteyn and Robert Cahaly saw Trump coming. In 2020, they see polls again underestimating his support.

value.title: Lil Wayne reveals 'great meeting' with Trump, prompting Twitter users to respond
value.excerpt: Lil Wayne made a big splash on Twitter after he revealed that he met with Trump, sharing a friendly photo the two of them took together.

value.title: Sean Hannity: Biden depicting ‘scary’ image of America despite surging economy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is making America out to be a country besieged by doom and gloom with five days left until the election, but “Hannity” host Sean Hannity argued Thursday the nation is actually on an upswing.

value.title: Trump meets with Army unit that conducted Al-Baghdadi raid, awards citation
value.excerpt: President Trump has awarded a citation to the Army special operations unit that conducted the 2019 raid resulting in the death of notorious Islamic State leader Abu Bakr Al-Baghdadi.
